    "All of these factors make the substantial impacts plausible.",
    "These magnitudes speak to the power of economics ideas.",
    "Perhaps the most similar evidence to ours is Azgad-Tromer and Talley (2017), who show that a comparable nancial economics training course inuenced the asset pricing decisions of energy regulators.",
    "Yet even brief exposure to economics can have an eect.",
    "In Ifcher and Zarghamee (2018), a brief economics lesson signicantly shifted choices in social interactions such as public goods contributions."
